<!--Row for the Aerial Imagery Services.-->

<div class="text-left" style="background:rgba(1,44,59,0.4); width: 50%; height:50px; box-shadow:1px 1px 10px black; color:white; font-size:20px; line-height:28px">
<b style="padding-left:10px">Aerial Imagery Services</b></div>
<br>
<p class="text-left">The OCTO Data team collects <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Orthophoto" target="_blank">Orthophotography </a>and now <a href="https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Lidar" target="_blank">LiDAR </a>data on a regular basis since 2000. The team was recently awarded a five-year aerial imagery services contract. Services include aerial photography, LiDAR, and updates to DCâ€™s base mapping layers with the most recent leaf-off product collected in Spring 2017. These aerial images have a variety of uses including web based visualizations and to create derivative data such as buildings, roads and elevation models. They are viewed in many District web applications and made available as downloadable files. They can also be accessed as web services to integrate into your own content.</p>
<br>
